Libvirt is an open-source API, daemon, and management tool for managing virtualized platforms. It works with various virtualization technologies, such as KVM (Kernel-based Virtual Machine), QEMU (Quick Emulator), Xen, and LXC (Linux Containers). Libvirt provides a unified interface to control these technologies, making it easier to manage virtual machines.

At its core, Libvirt communicates with the virtualization hypervisor and exposes APIs to manage VMs, networks, and storage. It can be used via command-line tools or graphical interfaces like Virt-Manager.

sudo apt update 
sudo apt install qemu-kvm bridge-utils virt-manager libvirt-daemon-system libvirt-daemon libvirt-clients qemu-system-x86 dbus
