sudo systemctl enable --now virtlogd
sudo systemctl enable --now virtlockd

apt install qemu-kvm qemu-system






Virt-Manager is a graphical user interface (GUI) that simplifies the process of managing virtual machines through Libvirt. It provides a rich, user-friendly interface to create, start, stop, and configure VMs, networks, and storage. Virt-Manager is highly useful for administrators who prefer managing their virtual machines through a GUI instead of the command line.




sudo apt update
sudo apt install qemu-kvm libvirt-daemon-system libvirt-clients bridge-utils virtinst virt-manager

